# Encryption configuration (optional)
# 
# You can encrypt the entire .env file OR encrypt individual values.
#
# OPTION 1: Encrypt entire .env file (recommended for production)
# 1. Generate a key: python -c "from cryptography.fernet import Fernet; print(Fernet.generate_key().decode())"
# 2. Save the key: echo 'your-key' > .encryption_key (or set ENCRYPTION_KEY env var)
# 3. Encrypt the file: python scripts/encrypt_env_file.py .env
# 4. This creates .env.encrypted - delete .env and rename .env.encrypted to .env
#    Or keep both and set ENV_FILE=.env.encrypted
#
# OPTION 2: Encrypt individual values (prefix with "encrypted:")
# 1. Generate a key (same as above)
# 2. Encrypt a value: python scripts/encrypt_env_value.py "secret-password"
# 3. Use the output in .env: BLUESKY_APP_PASSWORD=encrypted:gAAAAABh...
#
# Key storage:
#ENCRYPTION_KEY=your-base64-encryption-key-here  # Less secure (in process env)
#ENCRYPTION_KEY_FILE=.encryption_key  # More secure (file with restricted permissions)
#ENV_FILE=.env.encrypted  # Use encrypted .env file instead of .env

